1
00:00:00,440 --> 00:00:02,110
(All characters, locations,
organizations, and incidents...)

2
00:00:02,110 --> 00:00:03,510
(in this drama are fictional.)

3
00:00:03,510 --> 00:00:05,140
(This production followed
all guidelines for young actors.)

4
00:00:07,450 --> 00:00:10,820
Teddy bear, we're here to buy
a birthday present for Mommy.

5
00:00:11,520 --> 00:00:13,420
Sir, I'll take the gold ring.

6
00:00:14,120 --> 00:00:15,320
Can't go wrong with gold.

7
00:00:16,350 --> 00:00:18,320
So there was a recorder
inside the teddy bear.

8
00:00:19,320 --> 00:00:20,630
The audio isn't clear.

9
00:00:20,830 --> 00:00:23,530
If we send it for forensic analysis,
we might be able to recover it.

10
00:00:24,060 --> 00:00:26,360
The jewelry store owner's testimony
would be the most definitive proof.

11
00:00:27,430 --> 00:00:29,470
Let's find him. Whatever it takes.

12
00:00:31,270 --> 00:00:34,370
We have to prove
Ki Beom's innocence.

13
00:00:37,910 --> 00:00:39,680
I stole this from Ms. Young Chae.

14
00:00:39,980 --> 00:00:42,780
The original DNA test results
for Jin Tae Seok and Jin Se Hoon.

15
00:00:48,550 --> 00:00:51,690
So, Jin Se Hoon was just total trash
all along.

16
00:00:52,220 --> 00:00:54,060
I have to make Young Chae
divorce him.

17
00:00:54,730 --> 00:00:55,930
Please calm down, Chairman.

18
00:00:56,160 --> 00:00:57,260
Where did you get this?

19
00:00:57,500 --> 00:01:00,630
What? You're the one who told me
to steal it from Ms. Young Chae.

20
00:01:08,270 --> 00:01:10,340
Where's my mom?
Didn't you say she called for me?

21
00:01:12,680 --> 00:01:14,350
I was the one who sent for you.

22
00:01:15,310 --> 00:01:17,320
What? Why?

23
00:01:18,980 --> 00:01:21,290
You don't seem to like me lately,
Chef Hong.

24
00:01:21,790 --> 00:01:24,860
You always glare at me and comment
about whether I'm betraying Mom.

25
00:01:26,390 --> 00:01:28,260
I wanted to make you
something special.

26
00:01:28,860 --> 00:01:30,330
You've been craving meat lately,
haven't you?

27
00:01:30,730 --> 00:01:31,760
How did you know?

28
00:01:32,530 --> 00:01:33,900
I've been dying for some ribs.

29
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:39,970
I have some delicious beef ribs
all ready for you.

30
00:01:40,370 --> 00:01:41,370
Sweet!

31
00:01:57,220 --> 00:01:58,220
Found it.

32
00:02:05,660 --> 00:02:08,970
Grandma must have helped you.
No wonder.

33
00:02:09,130 --> 00:02:10,800
I did most of the work.

34
00:02:11,140 --> 00:02:13,510
All right, I get it. Here.

35
00:02:13,870 --> 00:02:14,940
Wait...

36
00:02:17,880 --> 00:02:19,240
You get over here right now.

37
00:02:19,510 --> 00:02:22,310
Or I'm going to the Kunhyang house.
Get here now.

38
00:02:22,650 --> 00:02:23,980
(Episode 89)

39
00:02:25,020 --> 00:02:28,420
Are you out of your mind?
What on earth are you planning?

40
00:02:28,690 --> 00:02:32,260
Se Hoon isn't Tae Seok's son,
so why fake the results to say he is?

41
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:33,930
If he isn't his biological son,
then Se Hoon...

42
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:35,960
loses his chance of becoming
the heir to Kunhyang Group.

43
00:02:36,830 --> 00:02:38,130
I can't let that happen.

44
00:02:38,730 --> 00:02:42,000
Whatever it takes, I will make him
the chairman of Kunhyang Group.

45
00:02:42,200 --> 00:02:43,870
And how do you plan on doing that?

46
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:48,740
Do you actually have feelings
for Jin Se Hoon?

47
00:02:51,080 --> 00:02:52,180
What am I going to do?

48
00:02:52,810 --> 00:02:53,880
I think I've lost my mind.

49
00:02:54,910 --> 00:02:56,150
I can't live without Se Hoon.

50
00:02:56,510 --> 00:02:58,720
Goodness. This is unbelievable.

51
00:02:59,150 --> 00:03:01,890
Jin Se Hoon is all flash
and no substance!

52
00:03:02,650 --> 00:03:06,560
Jin Tae Seok never had any intention
of making Jin Se Hoon the chairman.

53
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:09,530
- Let's get a divorce.
- I said no!

54
00:03:13,230 --> 00:03:15,170
(Kunhyang Group)

55
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:18,270
It took us a long time
to track you down.

56
00:03:18,700 --> 00:03:20,470
I closed down my jewelry store
a long time ago,

57
00:03:20,770 --> 00:03:22,240
and I've just been drifting around.

58
00:03:22,510 --> 00:03:25,810
I was just a kid,
but I remember your face.

59
00:03:27,850 --> 00:03:31,220
I've been keeping a low profile,
trying to forget it all.

60
00:03:32,450 --> 00:03:35,890
My dad was never able
to clear his name...

61
00:03:36,720 --> 00:03:38,360
and died after being
wrongfully accused for so long.

62
00:03:41,030 --> 00:03:42,560
Sir, I desperately need your help.

63
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:45,200
To prove my father's innocence.

64
00:03:46,700 --> 00:03:47,700
My dad...

65
00:03:48,830 --> 00:03:51,800
never even went near the place
where Joo Sang Cheol died.

66
00:03:53,040 --> 00:03:55,640
I told the police everything
I knew back then.

67
00:03:56,070 --> 00:03:59,410
And it was so long ago,
I barely remember anything.

68
00:03:59,980 --> 00:04:02,650
Sir, please, you have to help me.

69
00:04:04,080 --> 00:04:07,120
I have to clear my dad's name.

70
00:04:07,820 --> 00:04:09,620
I have nothing more to say.

71
00:04:09,990 --> 00:04:12,590
I have something
that might jog your memory.

72
00:04:13,220 --> 00:04:15,090
We had it restored by forensics,
so it should be very clear.

73
00:04:16,430 --> 00:04:19,730
Teddy bear, we're here to buy
a birthday present for Mommy.

74
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:22,070
Sir, I'll take the gold ring.

75
00:04:22,570 --> 00:04:24,040
Can't go wrong with gold.

76
00:04:25,370 --> 00:04:28,170
- This is...
- It's from the doll she had then.

77
00:04:28,670 --> 00:04:30,170
A recording that was still on it.

78
00:04:31,340 --> 00:04:33,440
At the very moment my father,
Joo Sang Cheol, was dying,

79
00:04:33,910 --> 00:04:37,180
Cha Ki Beom was in your store
buying a ring.

80
00:04:37,550 --> 00:04:38,620
This recording is the proof.

81
00:04:39,080 --> 00:04:41,650
How do I know if this has been
doctored or not?

82
00:04:41,850 --> 00:04:43,690
We've already had it authenticated.

83
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:46,760
And comparing it to a sample
of your voice will make it ironclad.

84
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:49,290
Isn't this just going to get me
in trouble?

85
00:04:49,660 --> 00:04:52,030
It's not like it'll bring anyone
back from the dead.

86
00:04:52,260 --> 00:04:54,600
For perjury
and destruction of evidence,

87
00:04:55,070 --> 00:04:56,800
the statute of limitations
has already expired.

88
00:04:57,500 --> 00:05:00,670
You won't be punished
for telling the truth in court.

89
00:05:02,140 --> 00:05:04,480
Look, I can't do it, okay?

90
00:05:05,010 --> 00:05:08,180
I don't want to get dragged
into something messy.

91
00:05:09,280 --> 00:05:10,720
How much did they pay you...

92
00:05:12,420 --> 00:05:13,420
to keep you quiet?

93
00:05:16,520 --> 00:05:19,260
Did that money make you happy?

94
00:05:20,390 --> 00:05:22,730
Happy enough to ignore that a man
was wrongly condemned?

95
00:05:25,860 --> 00:05:27,630
You were paid with blood money.

96
00:05:28,570 --> 00:05:31,340
That money could never
have brought you peace.

97
00:05:45,780 --> 00:05:47,850
You're always summoning me
at the drop of a hat.

98
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:50,990
You may be in the shadows,

99
00:05:52,190 --> 00:05:53,220
but you...

100
00:05:53,860 --> 00:05:56,090
are practically the chairman
of Kunhyang Group yourself.

101
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:58,030
Well, I suppose that's true.

102
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:01,800
What's so important that the "light"
and "shadow" chairmen must decide?

103
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,600
The murder of Joo Sang Cheol.

104
00:06:04,440 --> 00:06:06,470
Don't you think it's about time
we revealed the truth?

105
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:11,440
What? You want me to go to court
and say Cha Ki Beom is innocent?

106
00:06:11,740 --> 00:06:15,480
That I wasn't the one, and that
Jin Tae Seok was the real killer?

107
00:06:15,850 --> 00:06:17,750
You're asking me to confess,
aren't you?

108
00:06:18,520 --> 00:06:19,720
Because it's the truth.

109
00:06:20,420 --> 00:06:23,490
I even refused
when Ha Neul begged me to do this.

110
00:06:23,990 --> 00:06:26,420
What makes you think I'll give in
just because you sweet-talk me?

111
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:28,660
Forget it. I'm going to ignore that.
I'm leaving.

112
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:29,760
Do you know about it too?

113
00:06:30,430 --> 00:06:31,430
Know what now?

114
00:06:31,830 --> 00:06:34,530
That Se Hoon isn't
Jin Tae Seok's biological son.

115
00:06:35,700 --> 00:06:40,000
That conniving vixen.
How did she find that out?

116
00:06:41,510 --> 00:06:43,840
Oh, my goodness! I had no idea.

117
00:06:44,110 --> 00:06:46,640
Jin Se Hoon is
not Jin Tae Seok's son, you say?

118
00:06:47,110 --> 00:06:48,110
Oh, dear.

119
00:06:48,350 --> 00:06:50,150
What will you do?
You must've hoped...

120
00:06:50,150 --> 00:06:51,920
your son-in-law
would take Kunhyang Group over.

121
00:06:52,950 --> 00:06:53,990
If you're not careful,

122
00:06:54,420 --> 00:06:57,390
you'll be left high and dry,
Gong Nan Sook.

123
00:06:58,190 --> 00:07:01,330
I'll make them divorce immediately.
Se Hoon and my Young Chae.

124
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:02,790
You think Young Chae
will go along with that?

125
00:07:03,530 --> 00:07:06,530
Wait a minute.
What does Cha Ki Beom's retrial...

126
00:07:06,630 --> 00:07:10,840
have to do with Se Hoon not being
Jin Tae Seok's son?

127
00:07:12,740 --> 00:07:16,810
I'm reminding you, Gong Nan Sook,
that we're still in this together.

128
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:21,910
I'm going to take Kunhyang Group
for myself.

129
00:07:22,380 --> 00:07:26,480
I'll decide the line of succession.
And I will be the one in the light.

130
00:07:26,980 --> 00:07:28,520
And I'm supposed to be your shadow?

131
00:07:29,250 --> 00:07:30,250
Nice little rhyme.

132
00:07:30,820 --> 00:07:34,430
Who knows? Kunhyang's next owner
could be Cha Jung Won, or maybe...

133
00:07:34,890 --> 00:07:35,890
My Ha Neul?

134
00:07:38,530 --> 00:07:42,770
So even though I can't stand you
as the shadow,

135
00:07:43,130 --> 00:07:46,600
I should side
with the "light," Han Hye Ra?

136
00:07:47,940 --> 00:07:49,870
At least you're quick on the uptake.

137
00:07:50,410 --> 00:07:52,340
My shadow chairman, Gong Nan Sook.

138
00:07:59,150 --> 00:08:00,850
Se Mi. Are you making tea?

139
00:08:02,420 --> 00:08:05,090
I was hoping
to have some with you, Dad.

140
00:08:06,020 --> 00:08:07,020
I'd love that.

141
00:08:13,230 --> 00:08:15,730
Is something on your mind, sweetie?

142
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:18,800
It's about Jung Won.

143
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:22,240
What about her?
Do you still not like Cha Jung Won?

144
00:08:23,510 --> 00:08:25,410
Do you want her to disappear
for good?

145
00:08:25,740 --> 00:08:28,450
Dad, I was wrong to think that.

146
00:08:29,180 --> 00:08:30,880
I had these terrible thoughts
without even realizing it.

147
00:08:31,950 --> 00:08:33,080
I regret it now.

148
00:08:33,720 --> 00:08:34,720
Oh, my sweet girl.

149
00:08:35,790 --> 00:08:38,960
It's only human
to feel that way sometimes.

150
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:42,160
- Don't blame yourself.
- Jung Won is your daughter.

151
00:08:43,930 --> 00:08:44,930
She is.

152
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:47,830
And that's why you're so upset,
isn't it?

153
00:08:49,030 --> 00:08:52,170
- I completely understand that.
- But it's not Jung Won's fault.

154
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:53,800
What?

155
00:08:56,140 --> 00:08:58,080
You're right. Cha Jung Won...
I mean...

156
00:08:58,610 --> 00:09:00,810
It's not like Jung Won had a choice
in the matter.

157
00:09:01,910 --> 00:09:03,550
Poor Jung Won.

158
00:09:03,920 --> 00:09:07,620
The dad who raised her was framed
and died unjustly.

159
00:09:10,090 --> 00:09:14,090
Se Mi, don't tell me
you think that was my fault, do you?

160
00:09:16,290 --> 00:09:18,130
I think they're just vicious rumors.

161
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:22,700
People are just jealous because
you're so powerful and amazing, Dad.

162
00:09:24,140 --> 00:09:26,440
- Right?
- Of course.

163
00:09:26,670 --> 00:09:29,140
I am just as powerful and amazing
as you think.

164
00:09:29,670 --> 00:09:33,310
And I love you more than anything,
just as much as your mother does.

165
00:09:33,340 --> 00:09:34,350
So then,

166
00:09:34,710 --> 00:09:38,080
you'll do anything I ask?

167
00:09:39,180 --> 00:09:40,280
Of course.

168
00:09:51,930 --> 00:09:55,000
You're such a nuisance.
Go on, get away from me.

169
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:56,770
You seem to have something
on your mind.

170
00:09:57,230 --> 00:09:59,140
You can tell me anything.

171
00:10:00,740 --> 00:10:02,970
This retrial for Cha Ki Beom.

172
00:10:03,240 --> 00:10:04,510
Why is it even happening?

173
00:10:04,580 --> 00:10:08,850
And what does Ha Neul have to do
with any of this?

174
00:10:08,850 --> 00:10:13,220
Of course. It's about who murdered
Vice Chairman Joo Ha Neul's father.

175
00:10:13,220 --> 00:10:16,890
- It wasn't me, I tell you.
- I know. It was Jin Tae Seok.

176
00:10:16,950 --> 00:10:21,730
Right, but how am I supposed to be
the one to say that in court?

177
00:10:21,730 --> 00:10:24,300
You're Chairman Gong.
If anyone can do it, you can.

178
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:28,030
Did Ha Neul bribe you or something?

179
00:10:28,270 --> 00:10:29,400
Yes, he did.

180
00:10:30,100 --> 00:10:32,440
He did? What did he give you?

181
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:35,170
That doesn't sound like Ha Neul.
He's not one to butter people up.

182
00:10:38,580 --> 00:10:42,250
Please give this to Madam Gong.
And don't tell her it's from me.

183
00:10:42,980 --> 00:10:44,280
Why don't you give it
to her yourself?

184
00:10:44,620 --> 00:10:46,150
This doesn't suit you.

185
00:10:47,250 --> 00:10:48,890
Why would someone like Gong Nan Sook
get sick?

186
00:10:49,690 --> 00:10:52,190
You're not someone who would crumble
over a mere tax audit, are you?

187
00:10:55,290 --> 00:10:57,160
I was touched!

188
00:10:58,930 --> 00:11:00,130
My Ha Neul...

189
00:11:01,330 --> 00:11:02,700
really did that?

190
00:11:04,940 --> 00:11:07,100
I absolutely hate feeling like this.

191
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:09,710
All warm and fuzzy and restless.

192
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:11,980
I must be losing my mind.

193
00:11:12,980 --> 00:11:15,910
This has to be from a lack of sleep.

194
00:11:16,410 --> 00:11:18,480
I'm going to bed. Good night.

195
00:11:19,250 --> 00:11:20,620
And don't you dare dream about me.

196
00:11:24,860 --> 00:11:26,690
Not even a real son
would be that thoughtful.

197
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:40,040
- Something on your mind?
- What?

198
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:41,710
It's nothing.

199
00:11:42,710 --> 00:11:44,310
You heard about the retrial request,
didn't you?

200
00:11:44,440 --> 00:11:47,550
Of course. The Kunhyang family
is in an uproar because of that.

201
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:50,750
And now even Manager Hwang
has stepped up to testify.

202
00:11:51,280 --> 00:11:52,620
It's a total mess.

203
00:11:53,350 --> 00:11:54,790
Se Hoon, you need to stay out of it.

204
00:11:55,190 --> 00:11:57,490
- What?
- Stay out of the retrial...

205
00:11:57,490 --> 00:12:00,490
and don't worry whether
Cha Ki Beom is innocent or not.

206
00:12:00,560 --> 00:12:01,760
How can you even say that?

207
00:12:02,390 --> 00:12:04,260
If Cha Ki Beom is proven innocent,

208
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:07,360
then it'll be a piece of cake
to prove my father's the culprit.

209
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:10,670
The statute of limitations ran out,
so he won't be legally punished.

210
00:12:10,770 --> 00:12:12,200
That may be true,

211
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:15,110
but it would be a huge blow
to Kunhyang's reputation.

212
00:12:15,370 --> 00:12:16,670
Kunhyang would be badly shaken.

213
00:12:16,670 --> 00:12:19,610
Couldn't this be your chance?

214
00:12:20,280 --> 00:12:21,280
What are you talking about?

215
00:12:21,280 --> 00:12:23,480
The Kunhyang your father led
is sinking now.

216
00:12:24,080 --> 00:12:25,520
This is the perfect opportunity.

217
00:12:26,750 --> 00:12:28,350
Or an even bigger crisis.

218
00:12:28,890 --> 00:12:32,760
What if I help my father
and in turn, he promotes me?

219
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:36,590
- Listen, that's not how it works!
- Why are you getting mad?

220
00:12:37,160 --> 00:12:39,930
Young Chae, you've crossed a line.
A serious one.

221
00:12:40,230 --> 00:12:42,130
Kunhyang Group
is Jin Tae Seok himself.

222
00:12:42,270 --> 00:12:45,000
I am Jin Se Hoon, his son and heir.

223
00:12:45,270 --> 00:12:46,440
That's non-negotiable.

224
00:12:51,640 --> 00:12:53,540
(Kunhyang Group)

225
00:12:54,110 --> 00:12:56,050
The outfit alterations
are all done, right?

226
00:12:56,850 --> 00:12:59,520
We've finished the fittings.
They're all ready for the show.

227
00:13:01,120 --> 00:13:03,750
Wait. Where is Ms. Joo Young Chae?
She's supposed to be working.

228
00:13:04,260 --> 00:13:07,690
Who knows what's distracting her?
It's hard to get a hold of her.

229
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:11,300
- She talked big about leading.
- I'm so sorry.

230
00:13:11,800 --> 00:13:13,830
I feel like I've just been a burden.

231
00:13:13,900 --> 00:13:16,030
We all know it's not your fault,
Director Jin.

232
00:13:16,770 --> 00:13:17,840
You do?

233
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:23,010
Joo Young Chae did that again?

234
00:13:23,210 --> 00:13:25,010
This must have been so hard on you.

235
00:13:26,210 --> 00:13:29,950
Joo Young Chae can't get away.
Forget her lack of skill.

236
00:13:29,950 --> 00:13:31,720
She's always setting people up.

237
00:13:32,120 --> 00:13:34,690
We gave her so many chances,
but she played innocent to the end.

238
00:13:34,690 --> 00:13:36,720
Do you have any proof?

239
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:49,830
I saw her in the office that day.

240
00:13:50,270 --> 00:13:54,870
I felt Joo Young Chae would mess
with Ms. Cha's designs again.

241
00:13:54,940 --> 00:13:56,210
We'll head out first, then.

242
00:14:35,510 --> 00:14:38,980
Joo Young Chae is unprofessional
as a designer.

243
00:14:38,980 --> 00:14:42,050
That video made me so furious,
I couldn't even sleep.

244
00:14:42,050 --> 00:14:45,420
And to think I suffered so much,
believing it was my fault.

245
00:14:47,060 --> 00:14:48,330
This video...

246
00:14:48,730 --> 00:14:51,430
- I'll report this to the chairman.
- Not yet.

247
00:14:52,260 --> 00:14:55,130
We already tried
to discipline her internally,

248
00:14:55,170 --> 00:14:59,200
but Vice President Jin shut it down.
She'll find a way to get out of it.

249
00:15:00,970 --> 00:15:03,140
- Then what?
- Teach her an unforgettable lesson.

250
00:15:03,710 --> 00:15:04,780
A proper one.

251
00:15:12,620 --> 00:15:16,120
Keep it quiet until
the fashion show, even from our mom.

252
00:15:19,390 --> 00:15:24,030
That reminds me.
Mom wants us to spend time together.

253
00:15:27,730 --> 00:15:29,700
(Trailhead 150m ahead)

254
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:38,940
- So, you just wanted us to hike?
- Are you disappointed?

255
00:15:39,910 --> 00:15:42,880
- I like how simple it is.
- I like hiking too.

256
00:15:43,380 --> 00:15:44,380
You do?

257
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:48,490
Se Mi, you always used to complain
whenever I wanted to go hiking.

258
00:15:48,520 --> 00:15:51,790
I used to, but I like it now.

259
00:15:52,290 --> 00:15:53,720
Because you're here with Jung Won?

260
00:15:54,590 --> 00:15:58,000
I'm just so happy
that you seem all better now.

261
00:15:58,130 --> 00:16:01,430
Me too.
I'm happy we're out here together.

262
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:04,000
I hope we can do this more often.

263
00:16:04,070 --> 00:16:08,210
If we're going to do this often,
we have to come prepared, right?

264
00:16:09,510 --> 00:16:12,710
Ta-da! Let's each have one of these.

265
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:17,150
One for you, Se Mi.
And for you, Jung Won.

266
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:22,120
That's my mom for you,
always prepared!

267
00:16:35,970 --> 00:16:39,700
That's my girls.
Eat well and look after yourselves.

268
00:16:39,740 --> 00:16:42,910
- Your health...
- I know. I'll look after myself.

269
00:16:42,910 --> 00:16:44,010
Me too.

270
00:16:44,910 --> 00:16:46,340
Shall we start heading up?

271
00:16:48,810 --> 00:16:52,350
The retrial tomorrow will go well,
Jung Won.

272
00:16:52,850 --> 00:16:54,520
Never underestimate the power
of prayer.

273
00:16:55,420 --> 00:17:00,120
- I know.
- I'll pray it comes true too.

274
00:17:03,330 --> 00:17:04,760
All right, let's go.

275
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:21,650
So what's your plan for the retrial?

276
00:17:21,850 --> 00:17:24,820
What's there to do?
The statute of limitations ran out.

277
00:17:24,880 --> 00:17:28,590
Why pull this ridiculous stunt to
prove his innocence? How pathetic.

278
00:17:29,590 --> 00:17:33,990
They’re making a big fuss,
demanding I show up as a witness.

279
00:17:34,060 --> 00:17:35,060
Absolutely not! Don't you dare.

280
00:17:36,860 --> 00:17:41,170
You acted like you didn't care.
But you obviously do.

281
00:17:41,700 --> 00:17:44,570
- My reputation is on the line.
- Are you afraid you'll lose face?

282
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:45,840
Obviously.

283
00:17:46,100 --> 00:17:48,810
Gong Nan Sook,
don't you go doing anything stupid.

284
00:17:49,840 --> 00:17:52,610
Hey, that's my business.
I'll handle it.

285
00:17:53,810 --> 00:17:58,280
But Jin Tae Seok, why not
look at things differently...

286
00:17:58,350 --> 00:18:00,080
and think about it that way?

287
00:18:00,980 --> 00:18:03,150
How so?
What nonsense are you spouting...

288
00:18:03,150 --> 00:18:05,160
to convince me now?

289
00:18:06,020 --> 00:18:09,160
Just pretend I'm some mutt
that vaguely looks like me...

290
00:18:09,230 --> 00:18:13,160
barking as it passes by,
and just hear me out for a second.

291
00:18:16,370 --> 00:18:18,700
It's not like
you'll actually be punished.

292
00:18:18,700 --> 00:18:21,870
Being a coward isn't like you.
Why are you so scared?

293
00:18:22,170 --> 00:18:23,570
If it were me, I'd just...

294
00:18:23,640 --> 00:18:24,980
If it were you?

295
00:18:25,240 --> 00:18:28,980
- I'd just spill everything.
- What?

296
00:18:29,750 --> 00:18:31,420
Stop talking nonsense
and cut it out!

297
00:18:36,620 --> 00:18:40,760
But I'm not wrong.
He's all bark and no bite.

298
00:18:40,760 --> 00:18:44,960
Gosh, what a total coward.
How pathetic!

299
00:18:51,500 --> 00:18:52,700
About tomorrow...

300
00:18:53,900 --> 00:18:55,370
Do you think we can pull this off?

301
00:18:56,310 --> 00:18:57,310
Of course.

302
00:18:58,310 --> 00:19:00,580
We can prove
your father's innocence.

303
00:19:01,750 --> 00:19:03,250
So don't worry and get some sleep.

304
00:19:04,150 --> 00:19:05,280
You too, Ha Neul.

305
00:19:05,550 --> 00:19:06,580
Gosh.

306
00:19:07,780 --> 00:19:09,120
Right. Let's smile.

307
00:19:10,250 --> 00:19:11,420
It'll bring us good luck.

308
00:19:23,830 --> 00:19:25,800
(Court)

309
00:19:25,870 --> 00:19:26,970
(Witness stand)

310
00:19:30,810 --> 00:19:32,310
Twenty-five years ago,

311
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:34,880
I gave false testimony.

312
00:19:35,580 --> 00:19:37,710
I said I'd never seen them before,

313
00:19:38,520 --> 00:19:39,880
and that on the day of the incident,

314
00:19:40,250 --> 00:19:43,250
no father and daughter
came to buy a gold ring.

315
00:19:43,550 --> 00:19:44,720
And why did you do that?

316
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:50,030
A man named Jin Tae Seok
gave me a large sum of money.

317
00:19:50,660 --> 00:19:51,830
What was that?

318
00:19:52,260 --> 00:19:53,530
At the time,

319
00:19:54,130 --> 00:19:55,370
I was addicted to gambling...

320
00:19:56,030 --> 00:19:57,800
and was deep in debt.

321
00:19:58,470 --> 00:19:59,970
He offered to pay it all off...

322
00:20:00,440 --> 00:20:02,810
and even said he'd give me
a lump sum of cash.

323
00:20:03,110 --> 00:20:04,210
So I gave in.

324
00:20:06,340 --> 00:20:07,540
I'm sorry.

325
00:20:09,080 --> 00:20:11,780
Do you feel any remorse?

326
00:20:12,280 --> 00:20:13,320
Yes.

327
00:20:14,050 --> 00:20:17,850
Cha Ki Beom's daughter,
Cha Jung Won, contacted me.

328
00:20:18,220 --> 00:20:19,390
After a great deal
of soul-searching,

329
00:20:20,390 --> 00:20:21,930
I decided to confess...

330
00:20:22,430 --> 00:20:25,600
that I had committed perjury.

331
00:20:26,030 --> 00:20:30,100
- So he really committed perjury.
- I've heard of that before.

332
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:31,470
He has no conscience.

333
00:20:42,510 --> 00:20:44,650
What Jung Won truly wants...

334
00:20:45,480 --> 00:20:48,550
is to prove the innocence
of the dad who raised her.

335
00:20:49,320 --> 00:20:50,820
Didn't you say
the statute of limitations is over?

336
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:54,120
Can't you help her, Dad?

337
00:20:56,230 --> 00:21:00,660
- Is that so important to you?
- I feel bad for Jung Won,

338
00:21:01,600 --> 00:21:02,870
and I feel sorry for her.

339
00:21:04,840 --> 00:21:06,200
And you, Dad,

340
00:21:07,270 --> 00:21:08,870
can do anything, can't you?

341
00:21:15,250 --> 00:21:16,580
Around 11 p.m.,

342
00:21:16,780 --> 00:21:19,080
Honorary Chairman Jin Tae Seok,
the president at the time,

343
00:21:19,480 --> 00:21:21,390
received a call from
Chairman Gong Nan Sook,

344
00:21:21,650 --> 00:21:24,620
and urgently summoned me.
It was a construction site.

345
00:21:25,260 --> 00:21:29,330
Mr. Joo Sang Cheol was lying there,
bleeding from his head.

346
00:21:31,130 --> 00:21:34,830
- Was Mr. Joo Sang Cheol dead?
- No.

347
00:21:35,200 --> 00:21:37,870
He was still alive
when I checked on him.

348
00:21:39,970 --> 00:21:43,110
What happened next?

349
00:21:43,740 --> 00:21:45,380
Suddenly, Chairman Jin Tae Seok...

350
00:22:01,290 --> 00:22:03,660
Make it look like
that punk Cha Ki Beom did it.

351
00:22:04,830 --> 00:22:07,360
So I wiped the fingerprints
from the weapon...

352
00:22:07,760 --> 00:22:09,700
and planted it
in Cha Ki Beom's locker.

353
00:22:10,600 --> 00:22:12,300
All on
Chairman Jin Tae Seok's orders.

354
00:22:16,470 --> 00:22:18,510
I knew what I was doing was wrong,

355
00:22:19,040 --> 00:22:21,180
but at the time, I couldn't...

356
00:22:21,780 --> 00:22:23,250
defy Chairman Jin Tae Seok.

357
00:22:24,150 --> 00:22:25,250
I am truly sorry.

358
00:22:36,930 --> 00:22:39,960
Chairman Gong Nan Sook
isn't going to show up, is she?

359
00:22:40,260 --> 00:22:42,170
I wouldn't count on it.

360
00:22:52,340 --> 00:22:55,710
Ms. Gong Nan Sook,
please take the stand.

361
00:23:01,720 --> 00:23:03,190
Oh, gosh.

362
00:23:04,650 --> 00:23:06,260
Are you going in or not?

363
00:23:06,590 --> 00:23:08,490
I don't know!
How am I supposed to know?

364
00:23:12,300 --> 00:23:14,100
Just bite the bullet.

365
00:23:14,430 --> 00:23:16,230
The humiliation
will only last a moment.

366
00:23:16,600 --> 00:23:21,570
For your beloved son, Ha Neul,
end this trial once and for all.

367
00:23:22,910 --> 00:23:26,110
That annoying girl.
The worst part is she's never wrong.

368
00:23:30,880 --> 00:23:32,650
It's not like Ha Neul
supports the family.

369
00:23:32,650 --> 00:23:34,080
I don't know. I can't do it!

370
00:23:35,520 --> 00:23:38,560
- So you've decided not to testify.
- I don't know.

371
00:23:41,160 --> 00:23:42,530
Darn it.

372
00:23:46,130 --> 00:23:47,560
Ms. Gong Nan Sook?

373
00:23:48,570 --> 00:23:51,300
- I guess she's really not coming.
- What if she doesn't show up?

374
00:23:51,370 --> 00:23:53,300
You think she's trying
to get out of testifying?

375
00:23:53,540 --> 00:23:55,670
So does that mean
there's no more testimony?

376
00:23:58,640 --> 00:24:00,610
But the trial can't end
until the witness testifies, can it?

377
00:24:00,680 --> 00:24:03,680
- They called, but she's not here.
- Some witness she is.

378
00:24:04,580 --> 00:24:05,920
- Maybe she's stuck in traffic?
- I mean...

379
00:24:06,420 --> 00:24:08,820
The witness who was scheduled
to testify today,

380
00:24:08,890 --> 00:24:11,560
Ms. Gong Nan Sook,
has failed to appear.

381
00:24:19,430 --> 00:24:20,930
Wait a minute!

382
00:24:21,730 --> 00:24:24,870
I'm here! Gong Nan Sook has arrived!

383
00:24:30,810 --> 00:24:32,740
Hello, there.

384
00:24:32,810 --> 00:24:33,940
(Witness stand)

385
00:24:35,810 --> 00:24:39,550
- I didn't think she would show up.
- I did.

386
00:24:41,280 --> 00:24:43,790
You knew she'd come, Mom?

387
00:24:45,290 --> 00:24:48,830
Does your mom think
this is a fashion show?

388
00:24:50,660 --> 00:24:52,160
I think my mom has lost her mind.

389
00:24:52,260 --> 00:24:54,260
(Witness stand)

390
00:24:55,570 --> 00:24:59,040
I'm only going to say this once,

391
00:24:59,100 --> 00:25:01,140
so listen up.

392
00:25:02,270 --> 00:25:03,570
So,

393
00:25:03,570 --> 00:25:07,380
on the night of the incident
25 years ago,

394
00:25:07,840 --> 00:25:12,180
Joo Sang Cheol came home dead drunk,
as usual.

395
00:25:12,650 --> 00:25:14,890
And sure enough,
we started fighting.

396
00:25:15,120 --> 00:25:16,820
You wench!
You must have a death wish.

397
00:25:16,820 --> 00:25:17,820
- Fine.
- Fine!

398
00:25:17,820 --> 00:25:19,190
- Go on, kill me.
- Die, you wench!

399
00:25:19,190 --> 00:25:21,120
- Let go of me!
- Die, you wench!

400
00:25:27,530 --> 00:25:30,770
I thought I had killed
Joo Sang Cheol.

401
00:25:31,940 --> 00:25:33,700
I thought he'd stopped breathing,

402
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:37,110
so I sent an SOS
to Chairman Jin Tae Seok.

403
00:25:37,610 --> 00:25:40,580
President Jin,
there's been an accident.

404
00:25:41,110 --> 00:25:42,580
You have to help me.

405
00:25:43,310 --> 00:25:46,880
For 25 years,
I thought I killed Joo Sang Cheol.

406
00:25:47,050 --> 00:25:49,890
Do you know how guilty I've felt
toward my son, Ha Neul?

407
00:25:54,890 --> 00:25:59,000
I only recently found out
that Jin Tae Seok did it.

408
00:25:59,260 --> 00:26:01,360
Jin Tae Seok tricked me too!

409
00:26:01,530 --> 00:26:04,300
Is there any particular reason
you decided to testify?

410
00:26:04,770 --> 00:26:05,770
Was it perhaps...

411
00:26:06,470 --> 00:26:10,140
- your conscience...
- Conscience? No, that's not it.

412
00:26:10,510 --> 00:26:14,280
Cha Ki Beom must be proven innocent
to catch the real killer, right?

413
00:26:14,510 --> 00:26:16,680
And that's what my son,
Ha Neul, wants.

414
00:26:20,150 --> 00:26:21,720
And most importantly,

415
00:26:22,790 --> 00:26:23,850
I was humiliated.

416
00:26:28,020 --> 00:26:30,760
My nickname
is Gong Sol Jik, as in "honest."

417
00:26:31,090 --> 00:26:34,900
Hiding things and keeping secrets,
that's just not my style.

418
00:26:35,100 --> 00:26:38,130
The statute of limitations is up,
so I won't be punished, right?

419
00:26:38,130 --> 00:26:40,940
So why should I cover up
what Jin Tae Seok did?

420
00:26:41,270 --> 00:26:43,270
It's just humiliating for me, right?

421
00:26:56,120 --> 00:26:57,350
Your Honor.

422
00:26:57,890 --> 00:27:00,020
Twenty-five years ago,
Mr. Cha Ki Beom...

423
00:27:00,560 --> 00:27:03,790
was falsely accused of murdering
Mr. Joo Sang Cheol,

424
00:27:03,860 --> 00:27:05,530
and served time for that murder.

425
00:27:05,830 --> 00:27:09,000
However, the witness testimonies
and circumstantial evidence...

426
00:27:09,200 --> 00:27:12,940
all prove that Mr. Cha Ki Beom
is innocent.

427
00:27:27,320 --> 00:27:31,760
We ask for a just and wise verdict.

428
00:27:32,060 --> 00:27:33,690
We earnestly ask this of you.

429
00:27:43,200 --> 00:27:46,040
Honorary Chairman Jin Tae Seok
is on his way to the courtroom.

430
00:27:57,910 --> 00:27:59,680
Enough with this waste of time.

431
00:28:10,760 --> 00:28:13,160
(Witness stand)

432
00:28:13,160 --> 00:28:15,030
What happened 25 years ago...

433
00:28:15,830 --> 00:28:17,600
was a momentary lapse in judgment.

434
00:28:20,070 --> 00:28:22,670
Mr. Cha Ki Beom is,
in fact, innocent.

435
00:28:25,080 --> 00:28:26,080
I...

436
00:28:28,110 --> 00:28:29,780
am the one who killed
Joo Sang Cheol.

437
00:29:04,880 --> 00:29:07,750
(A Graceful Liar)

438
00:29:29,840 --> 00:29:34,140
Cha Jung Won, why meddle in my life
and get in my way at every turn?

439
00:29:34,510 --> 00:29:37,350
What now? The show's tomorrow.

440
00:29:37,350 --> 00:29:38,350
Who would do something like this?

441
00:29:38,410 --> 00:29:41,580
- For now, we have to be enemies.
- Enemies?

442
00:29:41,650 --> 00:29:45,190
Hye Ra must have been so desperate
to fake that crash 25 years ago.

443
00:29:45,360 --> 00:29:49,290
You wanted to join a rich family
so much you'd risk your life for it?

444
00:29:49,590 --> 00:29:51,960
You knew I wasn't his daughter.

445
00:29:51,960 --> 00:29:53,000
You disgust me.

446
00:29:56,000 --> 00:29:58,000
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
